Cicero describes these new ‘ collegia ’ as composed of all the dregs and slaves of the city. One motive for preventing large assemblages of such people is the same that exists now for putting down some fairs and merry-makings. These things which have had some respectable origin get corrupted in the course of time. There was also the danger at Rome from the slaves. The police of a slave country must be strict, or there will be insurrection.
